.TH xrd 1 "@XRootD_VERSION_STRING@"
.SH NAME
xrd \- XRootD command-line client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xrd
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIargs\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B xrd
utility is a native XRootD command-line interface intended to cover the common
file-management workflows provided by the GFAL command-line tools.
.P
Run
.B xrd --help
to list the available commands. The
.B archivepoll ,
.B copy ,
.B stat ,
and
.B sum
commands are implemented; the remaining commands currently expose help text while
their file operations are filled in incrementally.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B archivepoll
Perform an archive polling operation on the given URL.
.TP
.B bringonline
Perform a staging operation on the given URL.
.TP
.B cat
Concatenate a file and print it on the standard output.
.TP
.B chmod
Change file permissions.
.TP
.B copy
Copy files.
.TP
.B evict
Evict a file from a disk buffer.
.TP
.B ls
List directory contents or file information.
.TP
.B mkdir
Make directories.
.TP
.B rename
Rename files or directories.
.TP
.B rm
Remove files or directories.
.TP
.B save
Read from standard input and write to a file.
.TP
.B stat
Display extended information about a file or directory.
.TP
.B sum
Calculate a file checksum.
.TP
.B token
Retrieve an SE-issued token for a path.
.TP
.B xattr
Show or set file attributes.
.SH COPY OPTIONS
.P
.B xrd copy
uses the existing
.B xrdcp
copy implementation and accepts the same options. Run
.B xrd copy --help
for the complete option list, or see
.BR xrdcp (1).
.SH STAT OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Output version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose XRootD client logging. Repeating the option increases verbosity.
.TP
.B \-D, \-\-definition \fIDEFINITION\fR
Accept a GFAL parameter override for command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-timeout \fITIMEOUT\fR
Set the XRootD client request timeout in seconds.
.TP
.B \-E, \-\-cert \fICERT\fR
Accept a user certificate path for GFAL command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-\-key \fIKEY\fR
Accept a user private key path for GFAL command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-4
Accept the GFAL IPv4-only flag for command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-6
Accept the GFAL IPv6-only flag for command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-C, \-\-client-info \fIINFO\fR
Accept custom client information for GFAL command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-\-log-file \fILOG_FILE\fR
Write XRootD client logs to the given file.
.SH SUM OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Output version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Enable verbose XRootD client logging. Repeating the option increases verbosity.
.TP
.B \-D, \-\-definition \fIDEFINITION\fR
Accept a GFAL parameter override for command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-timeout \fITIMEOUT\fR
Set the XRootD client request timeout in seconds.
.TP
.B \-E, \-\-cert \fICERT\fR
Accept a user certificate path for GFAL command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-\-key \fIKEY\fR
Accept a user private key path for GFAL command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-4
Accept the GFAL IPv4-only flag for command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-6
Accept the GFAL IPv6-only flag for command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-C, \-\-client-info \fIINFO\fR
Accept custom client information for GFAL command-line compatibility.
.TP
.B \-\-log-file \fILOG_FILE\fR
Write XRootD client logs to the given file.
.TP
.B file
File URL to use for checksum calculation.
.TP
.B checksum_type
Checksum algorithm to use, for example
.B adler32 ,
.B crc32 ,
or
.B md5 .
.SH OUTPUT
The
.B xrd stat
output is formatted to match
.B gfal-stat
for the fields XRootD can provide: file URL, size, type, mode, owner, group,
access time, modification time, and change time.
.P
The
.B xrd sum
output is formatted to match
.B gfal-sum :
the file URL followed by the checksum value.
.SH NOTES
The command list mirrors the GFAL utility surface as a starting point for the
native XRootD CLI. The implementation will be filled in incrementally.
.SH SUPPORT LEVEL
The
.B xrd
command is supported by the XRootD Collaboration.
